values:
There was no reduction in the amount of work that I did, so it wasn't a genuine redundancy. You removed me from the organisation in bad faith because  [Insert your reasons - for example:
I raised a grievance which was unfairly rejected and so you now wish to get rid of me; 
I told you about unlawful activities going on in the company and you do not want to deal with them; 
I am about to go on maternity leave and you wish to appoint someone permanently to carry out my duties.]

There was no reduction in the amount of work that our client did, so it wasn't a genuine redundancy. You removed our client from the organisation in bad faith because  [Insert your reasons - for example:
I raised a grievance which was unfairly rejected and so you now wish to get rid of me; 
I told you about unlawful activities going on in the company and you do not want to deal with them; 
I am about to go on maternity leave and you wish to appoint someone permanently to carry out my duties.]

The redundancy consultation process was inadequate because [explain why. E.g. 'I wasn’t given an opportunity to propose an alternative structure in which my role could remain’; 
'I wasn’t given the chance to raise the possibility of working part-time'; 
'If given the opportunity, I could have identified the role of [name of role] in the organisation that I was also qualified to carry out'; 
'I could have suggested an alternative way of funding my role'.]

